reviewText: I stumbled upon this instant video and it's one of the best things I've seen in a long time. I actually watched it twice in one day.It is the story of a family who lived in the northern Alaska wilderness from 1960 to 1975(ish) - in the Brooks Mountain Range deep in the Arctic Circle, 250 miles from the nearest road and 70 miles from the nearest town. The film is comprised of home videos beautifully shot and narrated. It somehow conveys the experience of living in that glorious wild place, attuned and a part of nature; and of the inner transformation that gradually took place in them.It's a wonderful film, a real work of art.
Title: The Alaska Wilderness Adventure

reviewText: VERY BEAUTIFUL SCEANERY.  GREAT DOCUMENTARY ON ANIMALS ETC.  WILDLIFE IN THEIR OWN HABITATS IS A WONDERFUL WAY TO LEARN ABOUT THEM.
Title: The Alaska Wilderness Adventure

reviewText: Although I wondered what the reasons were to motivate this family to "escape" civilization the movie depicts their wonderful adaptability into a very harsh and unforgiving environment. It teaches the viewer how to learn new techniques in order to survive.
